news.headline: Earnings live: Netflix stock dives, GE Vernova reverses gains, Hilton rises as Tesla earnings loom
news.summary: The third quarter of 2014 is expected to be the best for the U.S. economy since 2009. The economy is set to grow by 0.4% this year.
news.article_text:
Earnings season is ramping up as Tesla (TSLA), Netflix (NFLX), General Motors (GM), and Ford Motor Company (F), among others, report results this week.

As of Oct. 17, 12% of S&P 500 companies have reported results, according to FactSet data, and analysts are expecting an 8.5% jump in earnings per share during the third quarter. If that figure holds, it would mark the ninth straight quarter of positive earnings growth but a deceleration from the 12% earnings growth reported in Q2 of this year.

news.headline: Can VZ Sustain its Subscriber Momentum Amid Growing Competition?
news.summary: Verizon generated $20.9 billion in revenues during the second quarter, up 2.2% year over year. Verizon registered solid broadband growth with total fixed wireless access net additions of 278,000. The company has been investing in improving its 5G infrastructure and capacity nationwide.
news.article_text: Verizon Communications VZ is one of the largest telecommunication service providers in the United States, offering communication services in the form of local phone service, long-distance calls, wireless and data services. The company operates in a highly competitive and saturated U.S. telecom market.
